Cristina Minasian is a fourth year Political Science and Communications major. She is currently the Political Representative for ASUCD Outreach Assembly. She was a former commissioner of the ASUCD External Affairs Commission, former Vice President of Communications for Pi Beta Phi and former UCD Panhellenic Delegate.

She was a participant of the Fall 2006 UCDC program where she interned at the Department of Justice, Office of Justice Programs, Office of Communications. She has also interned for the San Francisco District Attorneys Consumer Fraud Unit as a Consumer Mediator.
